\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li1440\ri0\lin1440\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch \'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i The Tribunal must conduct its hearing \'91as expeditiously as possible\'92 and \'91in accordance with the principles of natural justice\'92.   It may also conduct its hearings \'91informally\'92 or \'91in an inquisitorial manner.\'92   The trend towards inquisitorial proceedings
 arises from the concern that adversarial proceedings are unnecessarily drawn out and may lead to injustice where one party is able, for social and financial reasons, to secure more competent legal representation than another.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af0\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\i\loch\f2\i The hallmark of inquisitorial, as opposed to adversarial, proceedings is that the judicial officer plays an active role in the presentation of evidence and the questioning of witnesses and does not rely exclusively on the parties\'92 legal representatives to 
