justify its initial finding.   It is important to emphasise that this approach cannot, on any basis, be justified.   A court or tribunal cannot draft legislation.   If it does, it breaches the doctrine of separation of powers for it is the legislature\'92s ro
le to introduce and pass legislation.  It is trite to note that a court is required to interpret this legislation.   }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af2\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs24\lang1033\loch\f2\fs24\lang1033 
